 THE Smartphone Festival, a customer-reward programme of Nigeria’s telecommunications giant, Globacom, is back with more benefits for its teeming customers. In a statement by its head office in Lagos, the company said the festival is designed to offer subscribers who purchase mobile phones from any Gloworld outlet up to six months data as bonus. According to the company, customers who buy smartphones from any of its Gloworld outlets will have access to bundled data from 500 MB per month to 2GB per month for six months. The volume of bonus is dependent on the model a customer chooses from a wide range of phone brands, such as iPhone, Samsung, Infinix, Itel, Tecno and Imose. Globacom said the Smartphone Festival was designed to reward customers for buying their devices from Gloworld outlets. The company said its outlets nationwide are the best places to get the best price deals and accessories. Besides, Gloworld said the customers will also get free accessories on their choice devices. Globacom explained that the bonus data given to any customer under the programme will be automatically credited to the customer’s line and added to his or her existing data plans, which can be checked by dialling *127*0# or by sending SMS ‘info’ to 127.    The current edition of Glo Smartphone Festival will run till July 31. 